choices.text:
not being able to decide where to go or what to do. The options are endless, it is up to us seniors to enjoy life and be active.

St. Kits and Nevis’ programming for seniors aims to promote the inclusion of seniors in many leisure activities. St. Kits and Nevis pride themselves on keeping seniors active for as long as possible!

Check out this great blog post from a local teenager wanting to get involved with the soap carving Mark was talking about in the video- he’s trying to pass the carving skills on to the younger generation of students with the Soap Carving Club St. Kitts was created. There’s nothing like sharing history to communities and it starting at the smallest level, between the generations.

Thanks for visiting Kendra – so exciting to hear parents and their children are creating, sharing and learning together. We hope more schools will establish groups like this one you’re in.

I am so excited to see youth in St. Kitts 🙂 I have a friend travelling to St. Kitts this summer so maybe when I visit there we will find time for a little soap carving!

Kendra thanks a ton. The soap carving club has jumped to six members now, with the antique carving club all but dying. As an adult who’s been carving soap for over 15 years, I take great pride in keeping it alive and passing it on to the next generation. Can’t think of a better way to build literacy.

Hi Ian, you’re all the better for it
